Rollback the runner for Linux native builds
body:
At some point in late 2022; the `ubuntu-latest` tag in GitHub Actions started to point at Ubuntu 22.04.

Libraries built after this point won't load on older Ubuntu versions - the glibc dependency has moved to 2.33, but Ubuntu 20.04 (which is an LTS) only has 2.31.

We should explicitly build on the tag we want to support.

title: devolutions-crypto: fix native library preload on Windows
body:
Fix native library preload on Windows.

- `Assembly.Location` returns the full path for the assembly, it's necessary to call `Path.GetDirectoryName`.
- `GetExecutingAssembly` cannot return `null`; the fall back to `AppDomain.CurrentDomain.BaseDirectory` is not needed

Apologies for the churn; this was introduced in a last-minute refactoring

title: Devolutions-Crypto: add native arm64 support for Windows
body:
The goal is to support arm64 for RDM Windows.

- I added a native arm64 build for the proper library. 
- I moved the native library location on RDM Windows from {x86}/{x64} to runtimes/{rid}native

Rather than giving a relative path to the native library to the p/invoke declarations, instead we pre-load the native library in the static `ctor`.

Note that RDM's `build` and setup (`ai`) files will need to be updated for the new layout.
